DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Hey, Miss Xelvaria! Can we start training today?
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Limca

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Of course we can. Let's go to an open field.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Xelvaria

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Okaaay!
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Limca

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: We both went to the open field only several kilometers from the tavern.
Hmm, here should do. Well, for today I think of teaching you a simple spell. It might be a bit more advanced than what you've learnt so far.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Xelvaria

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Mmm, okay. I will be in your care then, Miss Xelvaria!
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Limca

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Me too. Let's do our best together.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Xelvaria

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Okay!
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Limca

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Well then, let's begin the training.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Xelvaria

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Miss Xelvaria then started explaining about the new spell. She taught me the basic formula of the spell and I repeated what she did.
Not bad. You can learn at such a short amount of time. You're very good, Miss Imca.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Xelvaria

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: It's because you're good at teaching, Miss Xelvaria. The oracle used to scold me because I often failed to understand what she meant.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Limca

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Is that so? Maybe the oracle is not really used to teaching other people. Sometimes, it's hard for genius to teach ordinary people, just as hard as you're following the genius' standard.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Xelvaria

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Ah, I see. Well, she's a genius and a real beauty. But you're also very beautiful, Miss Xelvaria.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Limca

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Eh? Is that so?
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Xelvaria

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Yeah! Mr. Igna is such a lucky person to have you as his lover!
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Limca

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Lover? Uhm, we're not, though I hope we are...
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Xelvaria

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Miss Xelvaria blushed.
Ah, I'm sorry for my rudeness, Miss Xelvaria.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Limca

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: You're not being rude at all. It's okay.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Xelvaria

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: She smiled warmly to me.
Well then, let's practice a little bit before going back.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Xelvaria

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Okay!
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Limca

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: We kept practicing on the spell for a while. After the sun set, we went back to the inn.
Long time ago, there lived in Arcadia, a powerful wizard named Odin. Odin had very powerful magic skills, enough for him to be regarded as Wizard King.
It is said that because of his great power, Odin became arrogant and abused his power in order to rule over Arcadia by working with the monsters.

Several powerful wizards from all over the country gathered to fight Odin and end his tyranny. Even though they didn't manage to kill him, combining their powers, the wizards managed to seal him away along with his castle deep inside the ocean.

The people of Arcadia could finally celebrate their freedom from the malevolent wizard. Peaceful time went for about two centuries before things started to change. The seal keeping Odin asleep has weakened considerably over the long time.
Sensing the dreadful sign of Odin's revival, the priest and the oracle gathered 3 people who had Stigmas, the proof of Odin's bloodline.

People possessing Stigma were feared because they were said to possess greater magic potential than ordinary people and their existence was said to bring misfortune. They were trained hard by the priest and the oracle in order to face Odin.
When the time finally came, Odin released a curse that would slowly turn all people into monsters. The priest wasted no time, and created a barrier to protect the people from the curse.

The barrier was able to protect the people, but they wouldn't hold out for long. The party made of three people possessing Stigma which were immune to the curse and had been trained by the priest and the oracle then embarked on a journey to defeat Odin in order to erase the curse.
C'mon guys. It's not that far away.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Cecil

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Good spirit, Cecil! Follow him, Imca! That's how a soldier should be!
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Galard

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Okaaaaaay......
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Limca

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Alright. Let's get going and quickly save Arcadia.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Cecil

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: It's quite unusual for you to be this spirited, Cecil. What happened?
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Limca

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Nothing in particular. I'm just a bit curious about this Oidn. That's all.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Cecil

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: The group kept walking and a moment later, they arrived had arrived in front of a large castle. The castle had an evil atmosphere around it. Seeing his destination, the party leader asked his companions without turning his back.
Ah, yes. We have arrived! Are you guys ready?
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Cecil

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Yes.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Limca

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Oooh! You can count me in!
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Galard

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Alright! Let's go guys! Let's save Arcadia!
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Cecil

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Yay!
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Limca

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Whatever! Just bring it on!
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Galard

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Ugh, it's so damn hard to open this doors.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Cecil

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Yeah, they're really heavy.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Limca

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Cecil and Limca were pressing the pair of doors in front of them with all their might. Even so, the doors refused to move even an inch.
You guys need more training! Let me open them!
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Galard

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Waaa!
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Limca

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Wait!
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Cecil

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Cecil and Limca immediately moved aside. Galard slammed the doors using both of his hands. The doors were broken with a crashing sound.
There you go.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Galard

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Thank you, Galard.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Cecil

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: As expected of our strongest member. You're impressive, Brother!
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Limca

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Well, you guys can leave this kind of things to me. The frontline is my responsibility, after all.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Galard

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Well then, shall we go, guys? Let's find Odin and stop his curse!
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Cecil

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Aye!
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Limca

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Yeah! By the way, where can we find him?
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Galard

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Usually the main bad guy resides in the deepest part of his castle. Well, if we create enough trouble, he will probably show up.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Cecil

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Okay.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Limca

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Well, let's go.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Galard

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Just as they walked, they saw a huge monster standing before the door. Noticing their presences, the monster proceeded to approach the party.
Careful guys, looks like he's quite different from the enemies we've faced so far.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Cecil

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Well, he definitely looks stronger than the bunch we've fought.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Galard

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Wah..... He looks so scary...
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Limca

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Heh? Who are you guys? Are you intruders?
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Gryphon

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: We're here to take Odin down! Tell us where he is!
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Cecil

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: It's been a long time since the last time ignorant idiots came to challenge our lord. Sorry, but I won't tell you where my lord is.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Gryphon

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Then get out of our way! We will find him ourselves.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Galard

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Don't be so arrogant, intruders! If you want to pass, you have to defeat me first! I'm Gryphon, the guardian of this area!
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Gryphon

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Heh, bring it on!
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Galard

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Your corpses will be my presents for lord Odin! Prepare yourselves!
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Gryphon

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Here he comes! Don't let your guard down!
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Cecil

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Uuuuuurgh! Guuuuaaaah!
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Gryphon

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Did we get him?
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Limca

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Careful, he might still be able to fight!
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Cecil

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Give it up! You can't defeat us!
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Galard

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Uuuuuuuuuurgh..... Damn it!! It's indeed my loss...
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Gryphon

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: So you admit your loss?
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Cecil

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: It's been a long time.... You guys are good! But, remember! There are still stronger guys waiting for you! And even if..... you manage.... to beat us all.... You will never.... defeat.... our lord....
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Gryphon

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Well, we'll see about that.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Galard

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Welll then.... See you in hell.... Ha ha ha ha!
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Gryphon

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: With his last burst of laughter, the one guarding the door fell to the ground.
He was a strong enemy. We barely made out of it....
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Cecil

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Yeah. And also, remember his last words about the guys stronger than him.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Galard

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Odin must be more powerful than them, right?
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Limca

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Obviously, but we can't back down. Even if we have to risk our lives, we have to defeat him at all costs.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Cecil

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Yeah, it's still too early to give up, anyway.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Galard

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Looking at her two companions, Limca's doubtful face was replaced with a smile.
Okay. As long as we're together, we won't lose, right?
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Limca

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Yeah. Let's go guys! It seems our journey in this castle is still quite far away!
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Cecil

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: With smiles, the party advanced further into the castle.
That day, Cecil went to train with his childhood friend while my Brother went to train with that scary old man at the mountain.
That leaves me alone. Uh....
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Limca

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: What are you doing here, Miss Limca?
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Xelvaria

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Hello, Miss Xelvaria. Are you by yourself?
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Limca

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Yes, because Master is training with Mr. Cecil. I'm here so I won't disturb him. I will come to him at the evening, though.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Xelvaria

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Um... I see... Say, Miss Xelvaria. Do you have any experience in magic?
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Limca

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Yes, I do. But I'm not as powerful as Master. My spells are more oriented for support purposes.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Xelvaria

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Can you show me how to do it? It's kind of boring because both Cecil and my Brother are not around.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Limca

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Miss Xelvaria smiled warmly.
With pleasure, shall we go, then?
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Xelvaria

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Okaaay!
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Limca

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Both of us then went out of the tavern to an open field. There, Miss Xelvaria demonstrated several of her spells. Her skills were wonderful.
Ah, that was a magnificent performance Miss Xelvaria. You're almost as good as the priest and the oracle.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Limca

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Eh? For real? Hurray!
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Limca

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Then, want me to teach you, Miss Limca. You also seem very talented.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Limca

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Of course. Master's friends are also my friends.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Xelvaria

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: But it doesn't feel right....
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Limca

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: What do you mean?
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Xelvaria

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Well, it's just not right for me to be helped by you just like that. Please, let me help you too!
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Limca

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Eh? Uhm.... But, I think I shouldn't get rewarded for helping a friend....
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Xelvaria

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Then, I also want to help you. That's because you're my friend, Miss Xelvaria.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Limca

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Well then, let's help each other.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Xelvaria

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Right!
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Limca

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Well, we can start tomorrow. Let's go back to the inn, Miss Limca. It's getting late.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Xelvaria

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Ah, you're right. Let's go back!
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Limca

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Both of us went back to the inn.
Hmm? Yo, Cecil! Fancy seeing you here? What? The kingdom asked you to stop the apocalypse now that they can't do anything?
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Igna

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: It's really you, Igna! Long time no see! How are you doing?
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Cecil

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Aargh!! Why do you always have to be so reckless?! Think about what will happen first before you do something! Honestly....
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Limca

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Understood. Thank you, Cecil.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Limca

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Let's go
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Limca

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Are we really going to be okay?
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Limca

choices.string: It's kind of hard to say for sure.
